DaVita Inc.

2000 16th St. 
Denver CO 80202 United States
Phone: +1 303-___-____
Fax: +1 303-___-____
http://www.davita.com





396
Managers




500
IT employees




$565.0MEST.
IT Budget




DaVita Inc., based in Denver, CO, provides dialysis and related services for patients suffering from chronic kidney failure. It also offers acute inpatient dialysis and provides a range of ancillary services to end stage renal disease (ESRD) patients.  In November… MoreDaVita Inc., based in Denver, CO, provides dialysis and related services for patients suffering from chronic kidney failure. It also offers acute inpatient dialysis and provides a range of ancillary services to end stage renal disease (ESRD) patients.  In November 2012 DaVita agreed to merge with Healthcare Partners.
DaVita Inc., based in Denver, CO, provides dialysis and related services for patients suffering from chronic kidney failure. It also offers acute inpatient dialysis and provides a range of ancillary services to end stage renal disease (ESRD) patients.  In November… MoreDaVita Inc., based in Denver, CO, provides dialysis and related services for patients suffering from chronic kidney failure. It also offers acute inpatient dialysis and provides a range of ancillary services to end stage renal disease (ESRD) patients.  In November 2012 DaVita agreed to merge with Healthcare Partners.  

IT Priorities:
• DaVita Inc. has increased spending towards data center technologies and network upgrades.
• Business intelligence and data warehousing initiatives are a strong focus for the organization in 2013.
• The company is virtualizing its server environment using VMware technologies.
• DaVita has implemented a limited bring your own device (BYOD) program and plans to expand it through the next 12 months.

IT Structure:
• The Corporate IT Department at DaVita, Inc. is led from the company's headquarters in Denver, CO and is being overseen by a Vice President of IT after the departure of the company's CIO. 
• The organization has large IT departments at its corporate billing offices in Brentwood, TN. A Smaller IT division is maintained in Boulder, CO.
• IT personnel in Tacoma, WA are responsible for data center operations and infrastructure.
• DaVita Rx is a subsidiary of DaVita, Inc. and has its own IT division that works with the corporate IT department. 

IT Vendors:
• DaVita Inc. has partnered with Cureatr to implement the vendor's mobile messaging platform.
• The organization works closely with IBM technologies.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013
• As of Q2 2013, DaVita, Inc. has virtualized 80 percent of its server environment using VMware technologies.

2012
• The organization upgraded its identity and access management technologies using Oracle.
• DaVita completed an enterprise-wide implementation of Workday's cloud-based human capital management (HCM) solution.





